00:09:03.850 --> 00:09:10.019
Lucy Johnson
In 1965 Lucy Ann Johnson, mother to a son,

00:09:10.019 --> 00:09:12.440
David, and a daughter, Linda, vanished.

00:09:12.440 --> 00:09:18.069
Her husband Marvin Johnson reported her missing
from their home in Surrey, British Columbia,

00:09:18.069 --> 00:09:24.480
near Vancouver, Canada, in 1965, but upon
further investigation police were alarmed

00:09:24.480 --> 00:09:30.029
to find that, after talking to various neighbors,
it seemed Lucy had not been seen since September

00:09:30.029 --> 00:09:32.269
of 1961.

00:09:32.269 --> 00:09:36.620
Based on witnesses reporting that Marvin had
been digging a septic field in the yard a

00:09:36.620 --> 00:09:41.720
few months prior, the Surrey Royal Canadian
Mounter police dug up the yard of the home

00:09:41.720 --> 00:09:49.420
which was located near 103rd Avenue and 145th
A Street in North Surrey, but found nothing.

00:09:49.420 --> 00:09:56.699
Lucy Ann Carvell, born in 1935 in Alaska met
her first husband Marvin Johnson and married

00:09:56.699 --> 00:10:00.170
in Blaine, Washington, later moving to Surrey.

00:10:00.170 --> 00:10:04.769
After reading a profile of her mother, considered
British Columbia’s oldest missing persons

00:10:04.769 --> 00:10:10.899
case, Linda evans, decided to take matters
into her own hands.

00:10:10.899 --> 00:10:16.100
Knowing that had her mother been alive she
would have been in her late 70s, Linda Evans

00:10:16.100 --> 00:10:19.130
committed herself to uncovering the truth
of her mother’s disappearance before she

00:10:19.130 --> 00:10:21.529
herself got too old.

00:10:21.529 --> 00:10:26.490
Linda’s father remarried after her mother’s
disappearance and later passed away in the

00:10:26.490 --> 00:10:32.749
late 1990s, and Linda’s brother David died
as a teenager, so Linda knew she was the last

00:10:32.749 --> 00:10:35.180
chance at finding out the truth.

00:10:35.180 --> 00:10:40.089
Utilizing the bare bones facts she knew, (Linda
was only seven or eight years old when her

00:10:40.089 --> 00:10:44.079
mother disappeared) Linda set out on her own
investigation.

00:10:44.079 --> 00:10:49.619
She posted an advertisement in a local newspaper,
the Yukon News near her mother’s birthplace

00:10:49.619 --> 00:10:55.709
giving her mothers name, birthdate, birthplace
and physical description (5’5, olive complexion,

00:10:55.709 --> 00:10:58.760
dark hair) as well as her grandparents names.

00:10:58.760 --> 00:11:03.740
Linda hoped to make contact with somebody,
anybody, who might know her mother’s fate.

00:11:03.740 --> 00:11:09.430
In 2013, Shortly after posting the ad she
received a call from a woman from Yukon, in

00:11:09.430 --> 00:11:14.430
the Northwesten Territory of Canada, next
to Alaska, who believed that Linda’s mother

00:11:14.430 --> 00:11:16.470
might be her mother as well.

00:11:16.470 --> 00:11:21.079
Linda was shocked to find that her mother
was not only alive but that she had a new

00:11:21.079 --> 00:11:24.550
family, With three sons and one daughter.

00:11:24.550 --> 00:11:30.160
Weeks later, Linda flew that 1,200 miles from
Vancouver to the Yukon Territory where her

00:11:30.160 --> 00:11:31.749
mother now resides.

00:11:31.749 --> 00:11:36.860
When asked why she vanished, Johnson claimed
that her husband Marvin, Linda’s father,

00:11:36.860 --> 00:11:41.959
deceased in the late 90s, was abusive and
unfaithful and unscrupulously banned her from

00:11:41.959 --> 00:11:44.559
the house without informing the children.

00:11:44.559 --> 00:11:48.630
Linda is not sure if she believes the story
as it seems highly unlikely that a mother

00:11:48.630 --> 00:11:54.389
would leave her children so voluntarily.

00:11:54.389 --> 00:11:59.240
Linda was skeptical at first but she ended
up believing her mother.

00:11:59.240 --> 00:12:05.499
Linda, now in her late fifties, is considering
moving to the Yukon Territory to Live near

00:12:05.499 --> 00:12:08.139
her mother and make the most of their years
left together.

